2. **Theoretical Model Reconstruction**: Reconstruct the Trenti et al. (2015) Fig. 3 (top panel) by calculating the halo formation rate for atomic cooling halos ($T_{vir} \geq 10^4$ K). Use the Press-Schechter formalism to derive the number density of halos with mass $M_{halo} \approx 10^7 - 10^8 M_{\odot}$ as a function of redshift. Plot this theoretical curve as the baseline for the GC formation epoch distribution.

3. **Formation Redshift Mapping**: For every GC in the GEMS and Sparkler datasets, calculate the formation redshift ($z_{form}$) based on the observed age and the observed redshift ($z_{obs}$). Use the cosmological framework to solve for the redshift at which the universe's age was equal to the age of the universe at $z_{obs}$ minus the GC age. Propagate the provided age errors to determine the uncertainty range for each $z_{form}$.

