5. **Statistical Characterization**: Compute the mean, median, and standard deviation for stellar mass, metallicity, and $z_{form}$ for both the GEMS and Sparkler systems. Perform a Kolmogorov-Smirnov (K-S) test to compare the $z_{form}$ distributions of the two systems against each other and against the theoretical model distribution to quantify the degree of overlap.

6. **Chemical Enrichment Analysis**: Perform a Spearman rank correlation analysis between the metallicity ([Z/H]) and the calculated $z_{form}$ for the combined dataset. This will test whether clusters formed at higher redshifts exhibit lower metallicities, consistent with the hierarchical enrichment expectations of the LCDM framework.

